<!-- Game Description Table -->

<table class="tablestyle" id="table14" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td class="sectional">

<!-- Game Description Header -->
		
		<table class="headertable" id="table15" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
			<tr>
				<td class="headercell">
				<img border="0" src="../../../images/headers/gamedes.jpg" width="240" height="33"></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>Mahjong is a game for four players that originated in China. It was called, meaning sparrow in ancient China, which is still the name most commonly used in some southern Chinese dialects such as Cantonese and Minnan, as well as in Japanese. However, most Mandarin-speaking Chinese now call the game má jiàng.
                  <br><br>Mahjong involves skill, strategy, and calculation, as well as a certain degree of luck (depending on the variation played, luck can be anything from a minor to a dominant factor in winning). In Asia, mahjong is also popularly played as a gambling game. In the game, each player is dealt either thirteen or sixteen tiles in a hand, depending on the variation being played. On their turn, players draw a tile and discard one, with the goal of making four or five melds (also depending on the variation) and one pair, or "head". Winning comes "on the draw" by drawing a new or discarded tile that completes the hand. Thus, a winning hand actually contains fourteen (or seventeen) tiles.
                  <br><br>Tensen Nyannyan Gekigyouban is a adventure mahjong game in which the player controls a young girl that will advance through the adventure playing mahjong games against other characters that she will encounter during the journey,
                  <br><br>To advance in the game the player should win the mahjong games. The gameplay is the usual in a mahjong game and the game uses a first person perspective for the adventure and for the mahjong part.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>Was well received PC "Tensen Nyan Nyan" is arranged by the addition of new elements, appeared to PS become mahjong adventure. Full Voice specification famous voice actor of 19 people were enthusiastically through the whole book, to empathy. Killer Move by compelling animation is prepared in each character, you can also enjoy graphic nail-biting sex appeal packed If you win.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>First person perspective.</li>
			<li>2D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>Medieval Fantasy, mahjong & Anime themes.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

